“The body found in Westfield Mall on Wednesday morning was identified as 28-year-old San Francisco resident Frank Galicia,” the San Francisco Forensic Bureau said.
The San Francisco Police Department says the death has been classified as homicide and an investigation is ongoing.
The victim&#39;s brother, Luis Galicia, told ABC&#39;s KGO in San Francisco that Frank, a former serving line chef in Boston, got his dream job as a cook at San Francisco&#39;s Sons &amp; Daughters six months ago.
A spokesperson for Sons &amp; Daughters said they were &quot;shocked and depressed&quot; by his death.
“We are a small team that works like a close-knit family and will be sorely missed,” the spokesman said.
Our thoughts and condolences to Frank&#39;s family and friends during this difficult period.
Luis Galicia said that Frank had stayed in hostels at first, but recently &quot;Finally, things were going well for him.&quot;
&quot;He found an apartment, he dated a girl,&quot; Luis Galicia told KGO.
Luis Galicia said that he could not imagine anyone who would be willing to hurt his younger brother.
